Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Spray 9x5 inch loaf pan with cooking spray, and set aside. In a large bowl, mix together butter and SPLENDA(R), and then mix in egg, egg white, and vanilla; beat until fluffy. In a small bowl, blend bananas with buttermilk. Sift together flour, oats, baking soda, salt, and cinnamon; mix into butter mixture alternating with banana mixture. Stir in raisins. Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake for 50 to 60 minutes, or until done; cool for a few minutes before removing from pan.